                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Battery and Materials Inside Fence Can Be Toxic </p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">
                                 <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Avoid injury during startup. </b>
                              </p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "/>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Only authorized and trained personnel can enter the fenced area and work on the AGV.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Personnel must wear the appropriate PPE around the AGV.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">The AGV must be stopped before personnel can enter the fenced area where the AGV operates.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Observe all plant and equipment safety requirements.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Turn the AGV off if a safety or operational issue occurs.  Open the door to the fenced area to break the circuit.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The AGV has an <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">E-Stop</b> button on the left side, with an indicator light.</p>
               </note>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Turn off power to the AGV before working on it.  Then lockout-tagout-verify the power.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">When working on high-voltage assemblies:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Ground the supply cable after disconnecting the voltage.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Short-circuit the components, e.g., capacitors by means of a ground rod.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Only install original or Hegla-approved spare parts.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
